 </section>
 <section xml:id="introduction-configure-virtual-machine-manager">
  <title>Introduction</title>
  <para>
   &vmm; is an application with a graphical user interface that allows
   configuring majority of a virtual machine properties. You will learn how to
   configure your virtual machine using &vmm;.
  </para>
 </section>
 <section xml:id="requirements-configure-virtual-machine-manager">
  <title>Requirements</title>
  <itemizedlist>
   <listitem>
    <para>
     Any &sle;-based desktop environment with the &vmm; application installed
     and running.
    </para>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <para>
     At least one connection to a valid &vmhost; configured in &vmm; or
     &libvirt;.
    </para>
   </listitem>
   <listitem>
    <para>
     An existing virtual machine on the &vmhost; that is visible in the list of
     virtual machines in &vmm;.
    </para>
   </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
 </section>
